   THE STORY OF GRIFFITH JOYNER
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Florence Griffith Joyner twice smashed a world record on Sept. 28, 1988 as she blazed to a gold medal in the 200-meter sprint.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Griffith Joyner dashed to her second gold in 21.34 seconds, shattering the world mark she had set just 90 minutes earlier in her semifinal heat.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   In her 200 quarterfinal heat on Sept. 27, 1988, Griffith Joyner ran a Olympic record 21.76 seconds.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   Griffith Joyner, 28, is scheduled to run in the 400-meter relay on Sept. 23, 1988 and may compete in the 1,600-meter relay that day.
  </a>
